value.0: You look about you, suspicious, but see nothing.

This container is where the local merchant keeps the gold from his transactions.

*     *     *     *     *     *
Merchant Tills
In Nordock Rogue and Bard characters may attempt to use Slight of Hand to steal a few coins from a vendor's purse. Simply click on this object and follow the conversation. However no reward comes without risk so note that there is a small chance of getting caught each time you try and as an illegal act if caught you face potential jail time from the guards. But a canny escape artist should be out in no time. Characters wishing to become more proficient at this should train in picking pockets. Success can only be met at each till once per reset and if discovered you cannot attempt on the same till again that reset.
This is a skinning knife.  It is not very useful in combat but when used on a corpse can produce hide and meat.  Rangers also use it to hunt.
This is a bedroll.  You can use it by placing it on the ground.
This is a bedroll, to use it, drop it on the ground.

Greenfish are abundant in the seas that lap the coast of Nordock. While bland themselves, a concoction of pepper and other spices brings out a surprisingly tangy and pleasant flavor. This fish counts as a single food serving for resting purposes.
The kit is full of herbs, salves, bandages, and other useful material.  It may be used to stop bleeding, cure poison or disease, and increase the recovery rate of resting patients.
This is the primary tool thieves use to disarm traps and pick locks  It seems extremely well made
This is the primary tool thieves use to disarm traps and pick locks
This is an oil flask.  You may use it to refill a lantern, or try to light it and throw at someone
This is a standard lantern, you must refill it with oil every 6 hours of use.

This is a water canteen. No adventurer should be without one.

Target a source of water to fill the canteen, or target the ground near you while you are standing next to water.
